result.title: Week 2 Round 1 — Discussion
result.content:
You can discuss anything related to round here. Sorry for posting this late; I was asleep :P.

My question:

What is a more tight upper bound of number of divisors of a number than Is it O(logN)? I'm asking this because I've used binary search on rectangle areas on second problem. For each area that is tested in binary search, I've used an O(PossibleDifferentRectangleNumberwithThatArea * N * M) algorithm to check if it's possible. What do you think my time complexity is? And of course, it would be very nice if you could help me find out where the bug is. My Code

UPD: Now, I've understood that I've failed in many ways :D I've tried to solve static version of this problem which can be solved in O(NM) similar to biggest rectangle in histogram problem.
